BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Crossroads & Cyphers
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261014T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261014T213000
DTSTAMP:20260709T185512Z
UID:occ-1709@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Staged Reading
DESCRIPTION:An immersive theatre-and-live-music work tracing rap's lineage
  from work songs and blues to hip-hop freestyle.\n\nAn immersive theatrica
 l and live-music experience from Atlanta artists Alex Acosta and ANON The 
 Griot\, tracing the evolution of Black musical expression from enslaved Af
 rican work songs and Southern blues to contemporary hip-hop freestyle. Bui
 lt around two ideas — the crossroads and the cypher — it blends spoken
  word\, live instrumentation\, freestyle\, and theatrical narrative to exp
 lore how music has long served as a tool for survival\, resistance\, heali
 ng\, and community. Led by artists from Soul Food Cypher\, the piece prese
 rves cultural memory while introducing audiences to the historical roots a
 nd social significance of hip-hop.
GEO:33.7973338;-84.3881531
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T192102Z
LOCATION:Synchronicity Theatre\, 1545 Peachtree St NE\, #102
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://synchrotheatre.com/plays-events/new-play-development/stripped-
 bare/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hannah & Greta\, or The Cost of Livin' The Dream
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261021T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261021T213000
DTSTAMP:20260709T185512Z
UID:occ-1710@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Staged Reading
DESCRIPTION:A loose Hansel-and-Gretel retelling: two new grads chase inter
 net fame and a job that promises them everything.\n\nA loose adaptation of
  Hansel and Gretel following two recent college grads and would-be interne
 t-famous friends who fall for a job that promises everything — a decent 
 paycheck\, health insurance\, and a chance to actually use their degrees. 
 As the temptations pull them in\, they're forced to ask how much of themse
 lves they are willing to give up to live their dreams. A new work by Atlan
 ta playwright Bobbi Twiggs\, directed by Charis Sellick.
GEO:33.7973338;-84.3881531
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T192102Z
LOCATION:Synchronicity Theatre\, 1545 Peachtree St NE\, #102
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://synchrotheatre.com/plays-events/new-play-development/stripped-
 bare/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:My Daughter\, My Karma
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270414T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270414T213000
DTSTAMP:20260709T185512Z
UID:occ-1711@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Staged Reading
DESCRIPTION:Choreographer Hiroko Kelly blends contemporary dance and spoke
 n word to trace inherited values across immigrant generations.\n\nChoreogr
 apher Hiroko Kelly combines contemporary dance\, spoken word\, and origina
 l dialogue to explore intergenerational relationships and cross-cultural i
 dentity. Rooted in the second-generation immigrant experience\, the piece 
 examines how cultural memory\, care\, and inherited values move through th
 e body across generations\, asking how our ancestors' choices shape presen
 t-day karma. It considers the humanity and resilience of the immigrant exp
 erience\, and the cultural practices that tether us to identity across tim
 e and place. Directed by Jacque Pritz.
GEO:33.7973338;-84.3881531
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T192102Z
LOCATION:Synchronicity Theatre\, 1545 Peachtree St NE\, #102
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://synchrotheatre.com/plays-events/new-play-development/stripped-
 bare/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Welfare Queen
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270421T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270421T213000
DTSTAMP:20260709T185512Z
UID:occ-1712@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Staged Reading
DESCRIPTION:A two-person Southern drama: a food-stamp applicant and a rule
 -bound caseworker find how much they share.\n\nA two-person play set insid
 e a worn Department of Family and Children Services office in the contempo
 rary South. Through humor\, confrontation\, and spoken word\, it follows I
 dea Jasmine — a whimsical young woman applying for food stamps while pur
 suing her dream of opening a hair studio — and Masque Hollow\, a blunt\,
  rule-hugging caseworker nearing retirement. As their meetings unfold\, bo
 th women confront the stories they've been told about poverty\, motherhood
 \, and success\, until a public reckoning threatens the very office servin
 g families like Idea's own. A new work by Atlanta playwright Brazil Remani
 .
GEO:33.7973338;-84.3881531
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T192102Z
LOCATION:Synchronicity Theatre\, 1545 Peachtree St NE\, #102
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://synchrotheatre.com/plays-events/new-play-development/stripped-
 bare/
END:VEVENT
